HEADWORD: Instigation
<hw>In`sti*ga"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>instigatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>instigation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The
act of instigating, or the state of being instigated; incitement; esp.
to evil or wickedness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The baseness and villainy that . . . the <qex>instigation</qex> of
the devil could bring the sons of men to.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>instigative</ent>⟦br⟧
